A Ledger is simply a collection or store of financial accounts or information. A blockchain is said to be a decentralized, distributed ledger of verifiable transactions.

A blockchain is a distributed, decentralized, publicly available ledger of transactions that are verified.

# Blockchain properties
- Immutable: unchanging over time or unable to changed
- Publicaly Available: availble to anyone in the general public
- Decentralized: controlled by several local offices or athorities rather than one sinlge one.
- Distributed: shared or spread out
- Chronological: Strarting with the earliest and following the order in which they occurred.
- Irrevocable: not able to be changed, reversed, or recovered; final.